  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: yoshino_s_test_evil (npm)",
  "details": "The package's preinstall hook executes shell.js which establishes a TCP reverse shell to IP 152[.]136[.]32[.]206 on port 6677. It spawns /bin/sh and pipes the shell's stdin/stdout/stderr through the socket, giving the remote attacker interactive shell access on the installer's machine. The main entry point (index.js) is a decoy that prints \"Hello, World!\".",
